rComments: Professor DeLombard is one of the most intimidatingly brilliant professors I've ever had. I thoroughly enjoy her lectures, and she speaks with fire and passion.
she's my favourite. she knows her stuff and you actually learn something in her classes. if you read the books and contribute in class you're guaranteed to do well--it's as simple as that.
Not worth it.  Also, avoid her good frien, Professor Dan White.
She gives good and clear lectures but plays favourites when it comes to marking and class participation. If you get in her good books you're likely to do well.

Great Prof!  I thought her lectures were insightful and clear.  As far as 'easiness' is concerned, her assignments were a laugh! They were so incredibly easy that those who didn't at least get a B should not be in any English class
She's HARD and can be moody! a hard marker as well. and classes can be a snooze. I'd NEVER take her course AGAIN!!!
